label elders_office:

    scene bg elder_office

    #Display Elder and mossbit

    show mossbit back static:
        xalign 0.5
        yalign 0.57
        zoom 0.53

    show elder front static:
        xalign 0.5
        yalign 0.35
        zoom 0.54

    #Insert Diologue Here

    narrator "Mossbit and Elder where discussing Villages administarative matters: Cave Safety Protocols, the schedule for the Froggo Hotsprings,{w=2.5}{nw}"

    narrator "and a pointed inquiry about what items Gribble has been selling lately.{w=2.0}{nw}"

    narrator "But Mossbit had a different question on their mind.{w=1.5}{nw}"

    window hide

    mossbit neutral "Hey Elder... one more thing. Remember when Hoppo arrived?{w=1.5}{nw}"

    mossbit neutral "You really snapped at Pebble for talking about the Surface.{w=1.5}{nw}"

    mossbit thinking "Weren't you a bit... too harsh?{w=1.5}{nw}"

    elder serious "What do you mean by harsh?{w=1.5}{nw}"

    mossbit thinking "What I mean is... no one in the village remembers what the Surface was even like.{w=2.5}{nw}"

    mossbit neutral "We just trust what you say. But we deserve to know.{w=1.5}{nw}"

    narrator "Memories flooded back to Elder Croakus of the clumsy young froggos growing up safely in their mossy huts, bringing life to the once empty cave.{w=3.5}{nw}"

    narrator "His weathered heart swelled with a fierce, protective love for all of them.{w=2.5}{nw}"

    elder closed "...{w=1.5}{nw}"

    elder closed "I guess I can’t really weasel my way out of this one, can I?{w=2.0}{nw}"

    elder neutral "Alright, Mossbit. I will tell you what I know.{w=1.5}{nw}"

    elder neutral "But you better not tell anyone else about this, you hear?{w=2.0}{nw}"

    narrator "Mossbit nodded in agreement.{w=1.5}{nw}"

    elder thinking "So... what I remember from those distant days is that I was very young back then.{w=2.5}{nw}"

    elder thinking "I wasn't an Elder back then. I was just a junior caretaker at the Great Froggo Daycare.{w=2.5}{nw}"

    elder neutral "We lived in peace and harmony on the Surface.{w=2.0}{nw}"

    elder neutral "New froggos arrived, and our numbers swelled. Beautiful mossy stone huts filled the skyline.{w=2.5}{nw}"

    elder neutral "But one day... it all changed.{w=1.5}{nw}"

    narrator "The Elder visibly shuddered.{w=1.5}{nw}"

    elder neutral "I don't know exactly how it started.{w=1.5}{nw}"

    elder closed "I was in the daycare building, tending to little froggos hopping about, when I heard high pitched screams{w=2.5}{nw}"

    elder closed "But they weren't screams for help. They were war cries. Screeches from the sky.{w=2.5}{nw}"

    elder neutral "I hopped out, and the village was burning. One of my superiors shoved a heavy object into my paws.{w=2.5}{nw}"

    elder neutral "The{color=#ffff00} Master Key to the Underground Shelter{/color}. They told me to evacuate the daycare and to hop as fast as I can.{w=2.5}{nw}"

    elder closed "As we fled, I caught a glimpse of it through the smoke.{w=2.5}{nw}"

    elder neutral "A {color=#FF1414}tall creature with feathers, wearing a purple hood and a cold, silver mask {/color} on its face. It watched us run.{w=2.5}{nw}"

    elder neutral "As we descended into the cave system, Shale, who was one of the few other adult froggos with us, grew silent..{w=2.5}{nw}"

    elder neutral "I tried asking what happened, but they murmured something about their friends... and then just gave me this long, blank, cold stare.{w=2.5}{nw}" 

    elder neutral "I tell you this so you understand that we can't return. I don't want anyone else to get hurt.{w=2.5}{nw}"

    mossbit suprised "...{w=1.5}{nw}"

    mossbit suprised "Elder... do you think that one day, someone might actually find a way back to the surface?{w=2.5}{nw}"

    mossbit neutral "I know it feels impossible. I've explored the mines countless times, and they're nothing but dead ends but still... perhaps?{w=2.5}{nw}"

    elder neutral "Well...{w=1.5}{nw}"

    elder neutral "There is another way.{w=1.5}{nw}"

    elder neutral "There is an old, locked gate behind the village that leads back to the surface.{w=2.5}{nw}"

    elder neutral "I hold the only {color=#ffff00}key{/color} to open it, but I will never reveal where it's hidden.{w=2.5}{nw}"

    elder neutral "We have safety, happiness, and nuggies right here, Mossbit... why leave?{w=2.5}{nw}"

    narrator "A heavy, uncomfortable silence fills the room...{w=1.5}{nw}"

    mossbit suprised "...{w=1.5}{nw}"

    mossbit suprised "...{w=1.5}{nw}"

    mossbit neutral "Hey Elder... have you seen Nuggy today? {w=2.0}{nw}"

    mossbit neutral "It’s been a while since I have seen them. Or their friends. {w=2.5}{nw}"

    pause 4.0

    return